-- Bug: a CLOSE PAGE microflow/nanoflow activity failed `mx check` on Mendix 11.12
-- with CE0117 "Error(s) in expression" at the Close page activity (the 11.12
-- nightly failed 02-microflow / 02b-nanoflow on the legacy engine this way).
--
-- Root cause: the legacy sdk/mpr writer serialized the CloseFormAction's page
-- count under the field name "NumberOfPagesToClose". The metamodel storage name
-- is "NumberOfPages" (modelsdk/codec already used it). Mendix <= 11.6 tolerated
-- the wrong name, but 11.12 rejects it: the real NumberOfPages field is then
-- absent and defaults to an empty expression -> CE0117. Fix: write "NumberOfPages"
-- (reader accepts both for round-trip fidelity on existing projects).
--
-- Any annotation on the activity (@caption / @color / @position) forced the
-- activity to serialize, exposing the field; a bare `close page;` sometimes did
-- not. Verify in Studio Pro (Mendix 11.12): the microflow's Close page activity
-- must load and check without CE0117.

create microflow MyFirstModule.ACT_ClosePageAnnotated ()
begin
  @position(200, 200)
  @caption 'Done editing'
  @color Green
  close page;
end;
